DCI sleuths based in Gatundu South have arrested a suspect for the offence of making public documents without authority namely land Title Deeds. Ng'ang'a Kanina was arrested on Sunday where 47 fake signed Title Deeds registered under different names were recovered from his house. The signed Title Deeds had purported to have been issued by the Land Registrars from Kiambu and Machakos counties. The detectives said that the fake land Title Deeds are suspected to be used by fraudsters to obtain money by false pretences from unsuspecting members of the public. All the title deeds have been retained as exhibits pending further investigations.  More to follow...